        byte[] get(byte[] key)
    throws IOException,
           TachyonException
        Gets the value associated with the given key in the key-value partition, returning null if the key is not found.
        Parameters:
        key - key to get, cannot be null
        Returns:
        bytes of the value if found, null otherwise
        Throws:
        IOException - if a non-Tachyon exception occurs
        TachyonException - if an unexpected Tachyon exception is thrown

      • get

        ByteBuffer get(ByteBuffer key)
        throws IOException,
               TachyonException
        Gets the value associated with the given key in the key-value partition, returning null if the key is not found. Both key and value are in ByteBuffer to make zero-copy possible for better performance.
        Parameters:
        key - key to get, cannot be null
        Returns:
        bytes of the value if found, null otherwise
        Throws:
        IOException - if a non-Tachyon exception occurs
        TachyonException - if an unexpected Tachyon exception is thrown

  throws IOException,
         TachyonException
        Returns:
        the number of key-value pairs in the partition
        Throws:
        IOException - if a non-Tachyon error occurs
        TachyonException - if a Tachyon error occurs
